    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-04T10:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-04T10:35:00-05:00" n="219"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.24/312: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-04T19:00:00+03:25"
                            >December 4, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 5—3 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>419. Food declaration was signed this afternoon by Foreign Minister, British
                    Minister and myself.<note n="75" xml:id="d219fn75">For text, see Department of
                        State Executive Agreement Series No. 292, or 56 Stat. (pt. 2) 1835.</note>
                    Text is substantially same as that given in Department’s 315, November 10 [<hi
                        rend="italic">9</hi>].<note n="76" xml:id="d219fn76">Not printed.</note>
                    British Minister and I simultaneously presented two notes to Foreign Office.
                    First informed Iranian Government that British and American Governments are
                    jointly arranging to bring into Iran 25,000 tons wheat. Second stated that if
                    Soviet Government wishes to participate in declaration a revised text will be
                    signed to replace present one. British Minister also presented note declaring
                    that declaration in no way diminishes British obligations under Tripartite Post
                        [<hi rend="italic">Pact</hi>] of January 29, 1942. Original of declaration
                    and copies of notes being forwarded airmail. Declaration will be published at
                    once in Tehran and London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
